{
  "text": "It has also been shown that bacterial protein L11 can bind in vitro to eukaryotic GAR rRNA fragment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In order to test whether this binding is functional in the cell, E. coli protein L11 has been expressed in a S. cerevisiae strain lacking protein L12. The results show that the bacterial protein is assembled into the yeast ribosome; however, its capacity to functionally complement the protein L12 absence is low, indicating that contrary to the RNA-protein interactions, the proteinprotein interactions are poorly conserved. Nevertheless, in spite of its low functional activity, protein EcL11 makes the yeast ribosome partially sensitive to thiostrepton.",
  "citation_candidates": [
